    <h1 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">AJK WAPDA Bill Check Online — Azad Kashmir Electricity 2026</h1>

    <p class="text-neutral-600 text-lg mb-4">Electricity in Azad Jammu & Kashmir (AJK) is supplied by the <strong>AJK Electricity Department</strong> — locally still called "AJK WAPDA" — which operates under the AJK government rather than the federal WAPDA. With consumers spread across mountainous terrain from Muzaffarabad to the Neelum Valley, the postal delivery of bills is notoriously slow. Bills printed in Muzaffarabad can take two weeks to reach villages in Leepa or Kel. Checking your AJK WAPDA bill online is therefore not just convenient — it's often the only way to know your amount and due date in time.</p>

    <div class="bg-primary-50 border-l-4 border-primary-600 p-4 rounded-lg mb-8">
      <p class="font-semibold text-primary-800">Quick Answer: Visit <a href="/ajk-bill/" class="underline">pakistanbill.online/ajk-bill/</a>, enter your <strong>14-digit AJK WAPDA reference number</strong> (printed on the top-right of any previous bill, labeled "Ref. No."), and your current bill loads in seconds. No login, no app, no fees — works on any mobile or desktop browser.</p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">What is AJK WAPDA and Where Does It Operate?</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">AJK WAPDA is the trade name of the <strong>AJK Electricity Department</strong>, headquartered in Muzaffarabad. Unlike the federal DISCOs (LESCO, IESCO, FESCO etc.) which were corporatized under WAPDA reform, the AJK utility remains a government department. It serves the entire territory of Azad Kashmir — about <strong>520,000 electricity consumers</strong> across 10 districts:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 mb-6 list-disc list-inside">
      <li><strong>Muzaffarabad</strong> — capital city, including Chattar and Garhi Dupatta</li>
      <li><strong>Mirpur</strong> — including Dadyal, Chakswari, Islamgarh</li>
      <li><strong>Kotli</strong> — including Sehnsa, Fatehpur, Daadan</li>
      <li><strong>Rawalakot</strong> — including Hajira, Abbaspur, Tatrinote</li>
      <li><strong>Bagh</strong> — including Dhirkot, Birpani</li>
      <li><strong>Neelum Valley</strong> — including Athmuqam, Sharda, Kel, Taobat</li>
      <li><strong>Hattian</strong> — including Chakar</li>
      <li><strong>Haveli</strong> — including Forward Kahuta</li>
      <li><strong>Sudhnoti</strong> — including Pallandri, Trarkhel</li>
      <li><strong>Bhimber</strong> — including Barnala, Samahni</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-6">If you live anywhere in Azad Kashmir, your electricity supplier is AJK WAPDA — even if your connection was set up decades ago. Bills are generated at the Muzaffarabad head office and the Mirpur regional office (for the southern districts).</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Step-by-Step: How to Check Your AJK WAPDA Bill Online</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Checking your AJK bill is fast and free. Here's the exact process:</p>
    <ol class="space-y-4 text-neutral-600 mb-6 list-decimal list-inside">
      <li><strong>Locate your 14-digit reference number.</strong> Open any previous AJK WAPDA bill. On the top-right of the page, just above the barcode, you'll see a number printed in bold labeled "Ref. No." or "Reference No.". This is your reference number — write it down or take a photo for future use.</li>
      <li><strong>Open the AJK bill checker.</strong> Go to <a href="/ajk-bill/" class="text-primary-600 underline">pakistanbill.online/ajk-bill/</a>. The page works on 2G/3G/4G mobile internet, so it's accessible even in remote parts of Neelum Valley.</li>
      <li><strong>Type your reference number.</strong> Enter all 14 digits carefully. The number is digits-only — no letters, no spaces, no dashes. If you copy-paste from an e-bill, double-check the first digit didn't get cut off.</li>
      <li><strong>Press "Check Bill".</strong> Your current month's bill loads in 2–5 seconds. You'll see the consumer name, address, billing month, units consumed, total payable amount, and the due date.</li>
      <li><strong>Download the PDF.</strong> Click "Download PDF" to save a copy of your bill. The PDF has the same barcode as the printed bill and is accepted by all banks and payment retailers in Azad Kashmir.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">What Information Appears on Your AJK WAPDA Bill?</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">The online bill is identical to the printed version. Key fields you should verify:</p>
    <div class="bg-neutral-900 text-green-400 font-mono rounded-xl p-5 mb-6 text-sm overflow-x-auto">
      <p class="text-neutral-400 text-xs mb-2">// AJK WAPDA Bill — Top Section</p>
      <p>┌─────────────────────────────────────┐</p>
      <p>│  Azad Kashmir Electricity Bill           │</p>
      <p>│  ┌────────────────────────────────┐    │</p>
      <p class="text-yellow-300">│  │ <strong>Ref. No: 01234567890123</strong>    │    │ ← 14-digit</p>
      <p>│  │ Consumer Name: [Your Name]     │    │</p>
      <p>│  │ Sanctioned Load: 3 kW          │    │</p>
      <p>│  │ Reading Date: 15-June-2026     │    │</p>
      <p>│  │ Units Consumed: 280 kWh        │    │</p>
      <p>│  │ Current Bill: Rs. 7,820        │    │</p>
      <p>│  │ Arrears: Rs. 0                 │    │</p>
      <p>│  │ Total Payable: Rs. 7,820       │    │</p>
      <p>│  │ Due Date: 30-June-2026         │    │</p>
      <p>│  └────────────────────────────────┘    │</p>
      <p>│  [████████ BARCODE ████████]            │</p>
      <p>└─────────────────────────────────────┘</p>
    </div>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-6">A special note for AJK consumers: your bill does NOT include the federal FPA (Fuel Price Adjustment) line item that appears on bills in other provinces. Instead, AJK bills show a separate "Mangla Surcharge" line for consumers above 300 units per month — this funds the AJK government's share of Mangla Dam royalty.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">How to Pay Your AJK Electricity Bill</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">AJK WAPDA bills can be paid through the same channels as federal DISCOs, but with one important caveat — some payment apps list it under "AJK" while others list it under "Azad Kashmir Electricity". Try both names if you can't find it on your bank app:</p>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
      <table class="w-full text-sm border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg">
        <thead class="bg-neutral-100">
          <tr>
            <th class="text-left p-3 border-b border-neutral-200">Method</th>
            <th class="text-left p-3 border-b border-neutral-200">Where</th>
            <th class="text-left p-3 border-b border-neutral-200">Fee</th>
            <th class="text-left p-3 border-b border-neutral-200">Notes</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="divide-y divide-neutral-200">
          <tr><td class="p-3">JazzCash</td><td class="p-3">App → Utility Bills → Electricity → AJK</td><td class="p-3">Free</td><td class="p-3">Most reliable</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3">EasyPaisa</td><td class="p-3">App → Bills → Electricity → AJK</td><td class="p-3">Free</td><td class="p-3">Quick confirmation</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3">HBL / UBL / MCB apps</td><td class="p-3">Search "AJK" or "Azad Kashmir"</td><td class="p-3">Free</td><td class="p-3">Reflected in 24h</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3">NBP branch</td><td class="p-3">Any National Bank in AJK</td><td class="p-3">Free</td><td class="p-3">Bring printed bill</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3">HBL / MCB branch</td><td class="p-3">Any branch in AJK</td><td class="p-3">Free</td><td class="p-3">Same-day posting</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3">Post office</td><td class="p-3">GPO Muzaffarabad, Mirpur, Kotli</td><td class="p-3">Rs. 20</td><td class="p-3">Slow — 2-3 days posting</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3">AJK WAPDA office</td><td class="p-3">Muzaffarabad, Mirpur regional</td><td class="p-3">Free</td><td class="p-3">Cash only</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-6">If a bank branch refuses to accept your AJK bill (this happens outside AJK), insist it's a valid WAPDA bill or use the JazzCash/EasyPaisa route. Mobile wallets always accept it nationwide.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">AJK WAPDA Customer Service & Complaints</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">For billing disputes, meter faults, or outages, AJK WAPDA operates regional complaint cells. Always have your reference number ready:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 mb-6 list-disc list-inside">
      <li><strong>Central helpline:</strong> 119 from any AJK landline, or 05827-920011 from mobile</li>
      <li><strong>Muzaffarabad region (incl. Neelum, Hattian):</strong> 05881-920155</li>
      <li><strong>Mirpur region (incl. Bhimber, Kotli south):</strong> 05827-920111</li>
      <li><strong>Kotli region:</strong> 05828-920144</li>
      <li><strong>Rawalakot region (incl. Sudhnoti, Bagh):</strong> 05824-920088</li>
      <li><strong>Online complaint:</strong> ajkelectricity.gov.pk (registration number issued instantly)</li>
      <li><strong>Email:</strong> info@ajkelectricity.gov.pk</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-6">Power-fault complaints are addressed within 4 hours in cities and within 24 hours in remote areas. Billing complaints take 7–14 days. If unsatisfied with the response, escalate to the <strong>AJK Ombudsman</strong> at ombudsman.ajk.gov.pk — this is free of cost.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Tips for AJK Consumers</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-3 text-neutral-600 mb-6 list-disc list-inside">
      <li><strong>Keep last 3 bills.</strong> In hilly areas, postal bills often arrive late or get lost. Previous bills have your reference number, which you need to check online.</li>
      <li><strong>Pay before the 25th</strong> of each month to avoid the late-payment surcharge of 5% and to skip the long queues at bank branches in Muzaffarabad and Mirpur.</li>
      <li><strong>Check your meter reading date.</strong> In AJK, meters are usually read between the 8th and 18th of each month. If you're home when the meter reader visits, verify the reading matches.</li>
      <li><strong>Report meter faults immediately.</strong> AJK WAPDA charges "average bills" for the months a meter is broken, and these averages are based on the previous year — usually higher than actual usage.</li>
      <li><strong>Apply for solar net-metering</strong> if you have a 3 kW+ sanctioned load. AJK gets excellent sun, and the AJK government offers a 30% subsidy on solar inverter cost for domestic consumers (separate from the federal subsidy).</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-heading font-bold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3 mb-10">
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">How to check AJK electricity bill online?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">Go to pakistanbill.online/ajk-bill/ and enter your 14-digit AJK WAPDA reference number. Your Azad Kashmir electricity bill loads instantly — free, no login required.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Which districts does AJK WAPDA cover?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">AJK WAPDA covers all of Azad Kashmir including Muzaffarabad, Mirpur, Rawalakot, Kotli, Bagh, Neelum Valley, Hattian, Haveli, and Sudhnoti districts.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">How to pay AJK electricity bill?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">Pay AJK WAPDA bill through JazzCash, EasyPaisa, or any bank app. Select Utility Bills → Electricity → AJK → enter 14-digit reference number. Also payable at National Bank, HBL, or MCB branches in Azad Kashmir.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">What is the AJK WAPDA helpline number?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">AJK WAPDA helpline is 119 from Azad Kashmir landlines, or call 05827-920011 from mobile. For power-fault complaints in Muzaffarabad region, call 05881-920155. For Mirpur region, call 05827-920111.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Why is AJK electricity cheaper than other DISCOs?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">Azad Kashmir has a separate tariff agreement between the AJK government and the federal government. Consumer tariffs are slightly lower than NEPRA's national schedule as part of the Mangla Dam royalty arrangement, but you still receive a bill that must be paid monthly.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Can I download a duplicate AJK WAPDA bill?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">Yes. Visit pakistanbill.online/ajk-bill/, enter your 14-digit reference number, and click 'Download PDF' to save a duplicate copy. The duplicate is identical to the printed bill and is accepted at all payment channels in AJK.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">My AJK bill shows a "Mangla Surcharge" — what is it?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">Mangla Surcharge is a small per-unit fee applied to consumers using more than 300 units per month. It funds the AJK government's share of Mangla Dam royalty. Unlike FPA on federal bills, Mangla Surcharge stays within AJK and is not passed to the central government.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">How to apply for a new AJK electricity connection?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">Visit your nearest AJK WAPDA sub-divisional office with CNIC, property documents, and a filled application form. Domestic single-phase connection fee is Rs. 1,500–4,500. New connections are usually energized within 30 days in cities and 60 days in remote tehsils.</div></details>
    </div>

